{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/javascript-convert-string-number/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Trainto.log()"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c166fedc-ba8c-51f2-a81d-44f600522fd9","excerpt":"There are several ways to convert a String into a Number.(or vice versa) Simple way This is the most simplest way. function Number() and String() functionâ€¦","html":"<p>There are several ways to convert a String into a Number.(or vice versa)</p>\n<h2>Simple way</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Number to String</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt1 <span class=\"token operator\">+=</span> <span class=\"token string\">''</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// String to Number</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'123'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt2 <span class=\"token operator\">*=</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// t2 += 0, t2 /= 1, t2 -= 0 all possible</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This is the most simplest way.</p>\n<h2>function Number() and String()</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Number to String</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">String</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// '5'</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// String to Number</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'123'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t3 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'10.5'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt3 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">Number</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t3<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 10.5</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>function parseInt() and parseFloat()</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'5'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">parseInt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'10cm'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">parseInt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 10</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> t3 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'10.5'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nt3 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">parseFloat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>t3<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 10.5</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>API definition of parseInt is like below.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>parseInt(string, radix)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>the radix argument is an integer between 2 and 36 which represents the base in mathematical numeral systems. Have a look at below examples.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token function\">parseInt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'1101'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 13</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">parseInt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'11'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 11</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">parseInt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'11'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 17</span></code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Javascript - Convert String into Number","date":"May 16, 2018","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/javascript-convert-string-number/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/javascript-map-set/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Javascript(ES6) - Map and Set"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/docker-mongodb-replicaset/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Docker - Setting up a MongoDB Replica Set with Docker"}}}}}